cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use pairo in your research, please cite it as below."
title: "pairo: LLM-powered entity resolution and record linkage"
abstract: >
  pairo is an open-source Python library for matching records across
  datasets — typically firms, products, or entities — using a two-stage
  pipeline: a cheap blocker (rapidfuzz / embeddings) generates candidates,
  and an LLM judges them with structured tool-call output. Designed for
  cases where pure fuzzy matching fails (renames, parent/subsidiary,
  abbreviations, lookalike-different-entity).
type: software
